---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Restaurant Marketing in Hamilton | Toronto Restaurant Growth"
  description="Hamilton restaurant marketing for the city's booming food scene. James Street North, Locke Street, and Ottawa Street restaurants — we help you get found on Google and fill tables."
>

  <main style="padding-top: 80px;">

    <nav style="padding: 16px 24px; background: #f5f5f0; font-size: 0.85rem;" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <a href="/" style="color: #E85D04; text-decoration: none;">Home</a>
      <span style="color: #666; margin: 0 8px;">›</span>
      <a href="/locations/" style="color: #E85D04; text-decoration: none;">Locations</a>
      <span style="color: #666; margin: 0 8px;">›</span>
      Restaurant Marketing Hamilton
    </nav>

    <section style="background: #1a1a1a; color: #fff; padding: 100px 24px 80px; text-align: center;">
      <div style="max-width: 860px; margin: 0 auto;">
        <p style="text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; font-size: 0.78rem; color: #E85D04; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 12px;">Hamilton, Ontario</p>
        <h1 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 6vw, 4rem); color: #fff; margin-bottom: 20px;">Restaurant Marketing in Hamilton</h1>
        <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; color: #ccc; max-width: 620px; margin: 0 auto 36px;">
          Hamilton's culinary scene is exploding. James Street North, Locke Street, Ottawa Street — world-class food is happening here. But most of these restaurants are nearly invisible online. That's the opportunity.
        </p>
        <a href="/contact/" style="display: inline-block; background: #E85D04; color: #fff; padding: 16px 36px; border-radius: 4px; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; font-size: 1rem;">Book a Free Google Audit</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section style="background: #fff; padding: 72px 24px;">
      <div style="max-width: 860px; margin: 0 auto;">
        <p style="text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; font-size: 0.78rem; color: #E85D04; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 12px;">The Local Food Scene</p>
        <h2 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.6rem); margin-bottom: 20px;">Hamilton: Canada's Most Underrated Food City</h2>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 16px; color: #333;">
          Hamilton's reputation as an industrial city is decades out of date. The Steel City's food scene has gone through a genuine transformation — driven by lower rents, a growing McMaster and Mohawk student population, and an influx of young professionals from Toronto who brought their dining expectations with them.
        </p>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 16px; color: #333;">
          James Street North is now one of Ontario's most interesting restaurant corridors — independent, chef-driven concepts that would fit seamlessly on Toronto's King West but pay a fraction of the rent. Locke Street South has evolved from a quiet neighborhood strip to a destination dining area with serious culinary talent. Ottawa Street's market corridor is becoming a weekend destination for food tourism from across the Golden Horseshoe.
        </p>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 16px; color: #333;">
          The problem is digital infrastructure. Hamilton's restaurant scene has world-class food and third-world digital presence. Most restaurants here don't show up in any meaningful Google search. The ones that get their digital house in order will capture the entire market — because right now, the competition for Google visibility is almost nonexistent compared to Toronto.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section style="background: #f5f5f0; padding: 72px 24px;">
      <div style="max-width: 860px; margin: 0 auto;">
        <p style="text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; font-size: 0.78rem; color: #E85D04; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 12px;">What We Do</p>
        <h2 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.6rem); margin-bottom: 20px;">What We Do For Hamilton Restaurants</h2>
        <ul style="list-style: none; margin-top: 28px;">
          <li style="padding: 14px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #e0e0d8; display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 12px;">
            <span style="color: #E85D04; font-weight: 700; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 2px;">→</span>
            <span style="color: #333;"><strong>Dominate Hamilton Search Before It Gets Competitive:</strong> Right now, ranking #1 on Google Maps for your cuisine in Hamilton is achievable in weeks, not months. We act fast to build that position before other operators catch on.</span>
          </li>
          <li style="padding: 14px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #e0e0d8; display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 12px;">
            <span style="color: #E85D04; font-weight: 700; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 2px;">→</span>
            <span style="color: #333;"><strong>Tourism and Day-Trip Capture:</strong> Hamilton draws day-trippers from across the Golden Horseshoe and Toronto specifically. We build content targeting visitors searching "best restaurants Hamilton" and "James Street North dining."</span>
          </li>
          <li style="padding: 14px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #e0e0d8; display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 12px;">
            <span style="color: #E85D04; font-weight: 700; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 2px;">→</span>
            <span style="color: #333;"><strong>Student and Young Professional Targeting:</strong> McMaster and Mohawk student demographics consume social media food content heavily. We build social strategies that reach this audience specifically.</span>
          </li>
          <li style="padding: 14px 0; display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 12px;">
            <span style="color: #E85D04; font-weight: 700; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 2px;">→</span>
            <span style="color: #333;"><strong>Review Foundation Building:</strong> Most Hamilton restaurants have under 100 reviews. We implement review generation systems that build this foundation fast — because in a market of low competition, a strong review count is a major differentiator.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section style="background: #f5f5f0; padding: 72px 24px;">
      <div style="max-width: 860px; margin: 0 auto;">
        <p style="text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; font-size: 0.78rem; color: #E85D04; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 12px;">Also Serving</p>
        <h2 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.6rem); margin-bottom: 24px;">Restaurant Marketing Across Ontario</h2>
        <div style="display: flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 24px;">
          <a href="/locations/mississauga/" style="background: #fff; padding: 8px 16px; border-radius: 4px; text-decoration: none; color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 500;">Mississauga</a>
          <a href="/locations/brampton/" style="background: #fff; padding: 8px 16px; border-radius: 4px; text-decoration: none; color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 500;">Brampton</a>
          <a href="/locations/etobicoke/" style="background: #fff; padding: 8px 16px; border-radius: 4px; text-decoration: none; color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 500;">Etobicoke</a>
          <a href="/locations/north-york/" style="background: #fff; padding: 8px 16px; border-radius: 4px; text-decoration: none; color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 500;">North York</a>
          <a href="/locations/vaughan/" style="background: #fff; padding: 8px 16px; border-radius: 4px; text-decoration: none; color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 500;">Vaughan</a>
          <a href="/locations/scarborough/" style="background: #fff; padding: 8px 16px; border-radius: 4px; text-decoration: none; color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 500;">Scarborough</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section style="background: #E85D04; color: #fff; text-align: center; padding: 80px 24px;">
      <div style="max-width: 860px; margin: 0 auto;">
        <h2 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.8rem); color: #fff; margin-bottom: 28px;">
          Hamilton's best restaurants deserve to be discovered. Let's make sure yours is.
        </h2>
        <a href="/contact/" style="display: inline-block; background: #fff; color: #E85D04; padding: 16px 36px; border-radius: 4px; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; font-size: 1rem;">Book a Free Google Audit</a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
</BaseLayout>
